      "translation": "Although measures to contain the spread of COVID-19 resulted in New Business Value declining to US$2.765 billion, sales momentum turned positive as mobility restrictions eased, and we entered 2021 with very strong momentum, with New Business Value in the first two months growing 15% year-on-year. Our large and growing portfolio of in-force policies, which generates high-quality and recurring income streams, drove a 5% increase in Operating Profit After Tax in 2020, while Free Surplus generated during the period grew 7%. As at 31 December 2020, Embedded Value equity reached a record high of US$67.2 billion, and the Group's local capital aggregation method coverage ratio stood at 374%, demonstrating our strong capital position and prudent financial management."
